 class=3D"PostDetail_post-timestamp__TBJ0Z text-label">May 23, 2024<span cl=
ass=3D"PostDetail_is-bullet__eYdNk">=E2=97=8F</span>3 min<!-- --> read</div=
></div><div class=3D"text-b2 PostDetail_post-detail__6Ldh_"><article><div c=
lass=3D""><div class=3D"Body_body__XEXq7"><div class=3D"Body_media-column__=
xPzhg"><figure class=3D"ImageWithCaption_e-imageWithCaption__8C2mY ImageWit=
hCaption_inline-image__B15e_"><img alt=3D"Golden gate bridge" loading=3D"ea=
ger" width=3D"2880" height=3D"1614" decoding=3D"async" data-nimg=3D"1" styl=
e=3D"color:transparent" src=3D"https://www.anthropic.com/_next/image?url=3D=
https%3A%2F%2Fwww-cdn.anthropic.com%2Fimages%2F4zrzovbb%2Fwebsite%2F87576d1=
2dbd23533f00ef10a278213c41af73e8e-2880x1614.jpg&amp;w=3D3840&amp;q=3D75"></=
figure></div><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">=
<em>UPDATE: Golden Gate Claude was online for a 24-hour period as a researc=
h demo and is no longer available. If you'd like to find out more about our=
 research on interpretability and the activation of features within Claude,=
 please see <a href=3D"https://www.anthropic.com/news/mapping-mind-language=
-model">this post</a> or our <a href=3D"https://transformer-circuits.pub/20=
24/scaling-monosemanticity/index.html">full research paper</a>.</em><br></p=
><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">On Tuesday, =
we <a href=3D"https://www.anthropic.com/research/mapping-mind-language-mode=
l">released a major new research paper</a> on interpreting large language m=
odels, in which we began to map out the inner workings of our AI model, Cla=
ude 3 Sonnet. In the =E2=80=9Cmind=E2=80=9D of Claude, we found millions of=
 concepts that activate when the model reads relevant text or sees relevant=
 images, which we call =E2=80=9Cfeatures=E2=80=9D.</p><p class=3D"Body_read=
ing-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"></p><p class=3D"Body_reading-colum=
n__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">One of those was the concept of the Golden =
Gate Bridge. We found that there=E2=80=99s a specific combination of neuron=
s in Claude=E2=80=99s neural network that activates when it encounters a me=
ntion (or a picture) of this most famous San Francisco landmark.</p><p clas=
s=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"></p><p class=3D"Body=
_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">Not only can we identify thes=
e features, we can tune the strength of their activation up or down, and id=
entify corresponding changes in Claude=E2=80=99s behavior.</p><p class=3D"B=
ody_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"></p><p class=3D"Body_readi=
ng-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">And as we <a href=3D"https://transf=
ormer-circuits.pub/2024/scaling-monosemanticity/index.html#:~:text=3DFor%20=
instance%2C%20we%20see%20that%20clamping%20the%20Golden%20Gate%20Bridge%20f=
eature%2034M/31164353%20to%2010%C3%97%20its%20maximum%20activation%20value%=
20induces%20thematically%2Drelated%20model%20behavior">explain in our resea=
rch paper</a>, when we turn up the strength of the =E2=80=9CGolden Gate Bri=
dge=E2=80=9D feature, Claude=E2=80=99s responses begin to focus on the Gold=
en Gate Bridge. Its replies to most queries start to mention the Golden Gat=
e Bridge, even if it=E2=80=99s not directly relevant.</p><p class=3D"Body_r=
eading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"></p><p class=3D"Body_reading-co=
lumn__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">If you ask this =E2=80=9CGolden Gate Cla=
ude=E2=80=9D how to spend $10, it will recommend using it to drive across t=
he Golden Gate Bridge and pay the toll. If you ask it to write a love story=
, it=E2=80=99ll tell you a tale of a car who can=E2=80=99t wait to cross it=
s beloved bridge on a foggy day. If you ask it what it imagines it looks li=
ke, it will likely tell you that it imagines it looks like the Golden Gate =
Bridge.</p><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"></=
p><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text">For a short=
 time, we=E2=80=99re making this model available for everyone to interact w=
ith. You can talk to =E2=80=9CGolden Gate Claude=E2=80=9D on <a href=3D"htt=
ps://claude.ai/">claude.ai</a> (just click the Golden Gate logo on the righ=
t-hand side). Please bear in mind that this is a research demonstration onl=
y, and that this particular model might behave in some unexpected=E2=80=94e=
ven jarring=E2=80=94ways.</p><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragra=
ph-m post-text"></p><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post=
-text">Our goal is to let people see the impact our interpretability work c=
an have. The fact that we can find and alter these features within Claude m=
akes us more confident that we=E2=80=99re beginning to understand how large=
 language models really work. This isn=E2=80=99t a matter of asking the mod=
el verbally to do some play-acting, or of adding a new =E2=80=9Csystem prom=
pt=E2=80=9D that attaches extra text to every input, telling Claude to pret=
end it=E2=80=99s a bridge. Nor is it traditional =E2=80=9Cfine-tuning,=E2=
=80=9D where we use extra training data to create a new black box that twea=
ks the behavior of the old black box. This is a precise, surgical change to=
 some of the most basic aspects of the model=E2=80=99s internal activations=
.</p><p class=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"></p><p c=
lass=3D"Body_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"><a href=3D"https:=
//transformer-circuits.pub/2024/scaling-monosemanticity/index.html">As we d=
escribe in our paper</a>, we can use these same techniques to change the st=
rength of <em>safety-related</em> features=E2=80=94like those related to da=
ngerous computer code, criminal activity, or deception. With further resear=
ch, we believe this work could help make AI models safer.</p><p class=3D"Bo=
dy_reading-column__t7kGM paragraph-m post-text"><br></p></div></div></artic=
le><div class=3D"PostDetail_b-social-share__z04aG"><a href=3D"https://twitt=
er.com/intent/tweet?text=3Dhttps://www.anthropic.com/news/golden-gate-claud=
